title: Google\Cloud\AutoMl\V1beta1\ClassificationEvaluationMetrics\ConfusionMatrix
name: ConfusionMatrix
description:
Confusion matrix of the model running the classification.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.automl.v1beta1.ClassificationEvaluationMetrics.ConfusionMatrix

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.annotation_spec_id
params.description: Output only. IDs of the annotation specs used in the confusion matrix.

params.name: data.row
params.description: Output only. Rows in the confusion matrix. The number of rows is equal to the size of annotation_spec_id. row[i].value[j] is the number of examples that have ground truth of the annotation_spec_id[i] and are predicted as annotation_spec_id[j] by the model being evaluated.
